CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, July 27, 1946, pg. 16, reads: "Syria Mosque is where the Frogs will gather Wednesday night for the colossal 'Night of Stars' presentation. Famous entertainers, who started out in Pittsburgh, are being brought back home to be honored by their appreciative home-town fans.  Among ...to be honored are Earl Hines, Maxine Sullivan, Mary Lou Williams, Louis Deppa, Billy Strayhorn and others."
TitMainTitle: Exterior of Syria Mosque with poster advertising "Pop Concerts, Little Symphony Orchestra, Victor Saudex,...Syria Mosque Lawn, July 9 - August 9"
